VALUES(10, 6, 'Learning Reusable Robot Skill Embeddings', 'Evaluations of deep reinforcement learning methods for robotics often include learning curves that depict a robot''s performance when learning a set of skills. These skills are commonly learned in isolation and from scratch, even though they might share a similar structure. This is particularly apparent in manipulation skills such as reaching and grasping. In contrast, humans reuse previously learned skills efficiently to learn new ones, e.g. by sequencing or interpolating between them. In this work, we present a first step towards learning robot skill embeddings that enable reusing previously acquired skills. Our results indicate that our method can interpolate and/or sequence previously learned skills in order to accomplish more complex tasks, even in the presence of sparse rewards.', '2019-01-24 11:05:00.000-08', '2019-01-24 11:25:00.000-08', 'FCFS_P', 5, 0, 'Grand Ballroom, 5 Embarcadero Center, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
