VALUES(36, 9, 'Diversity and Inclusion Can’t Thrive with Exclusion', 'More organizations initiate diversity programs every year that aim to employ minorities, women and those with disabilities. Yet, truly beneficial diversity must span beyond gender and ethnicity, while welcoming men to be ardent supporters. How do you thoughtfully design diversity programs to avoid unintended consequences and maximize their effectiveness?

